translation: From the Kanesh colony to Aqil-..., our messenger, every single and the trading stations: A tablet has come to the City.
When the tablet was discussed in the City. This day no one may bring the tin out of the profit, (for) no one may bring it to me. The Kanesh colony will take a tablet from the City.

Since you hear our letter, you have heard our letter, whether he has given as part of the palace or has obtained the palace or has not yet sold it. Whatever silver was sworn by the City, what was sworn by the City and what was sworn by the City and what was sworn by our messenger so I can write to our messenger so I can do you with our messenger.
The death of our tablets I sent to every single colony and the trading stations. Let us not obstruct me.
